      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Certainly! Small businesses in a town with a lower cost of living stand to gain from a higher minimum wage as residents have greater buying power. This can lead to increased patronage at your cafe unless the wage increase is substantial to affect your operating costs, which might not be frequent or as in a larger cost of living area. However, be prepared for possible price adjustments to ensure your business remains profitable without undue strain on the newly employed staff. Remember, the positive effect on your employees can improve morale and customer perception, potentially making up for any slight cost increase.",
